Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 03:33 PM Defendant Jason M Voivedich not in court.  Colleen Catherine Nordin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Court reviews events in file, advises defendant called their office yesterday saying he didn't have a ride to court. Court had JA advise defendant that he needed to be in court for todays hearing.  State advises defendant contacted their office this morning indicating he wouldn't be at hearing today. State requests bench warrant.  Court orders bench warrant, ECAR region.
Deferred prosecution agreement hearing on January 23, 2020 at 03:30 pm.

03:07 PM Defendant Jason M Voivedich not in court.  Nicholas Paul Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file, reviews State's motion to revoke DAGPA.  State indicates they have not received anything from defendant showing he's completed counseling as part of the DAGPA.  State requests another court date with notice to defendant of mandatory appearance or a warrant may be issued.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for January 23, 2020 at 03:30 pm.
State's Motion to Revoke Deferred Acceptance of Guilty Plea Agreement

11:49 AM Defendant Jason M Voivedich appeared by phone. Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews agreement, questions State. State has not received information that Defendant has completed counseling, requests 90 day extension to allow Defendant to complete counseling. Court questions Defendant, who questions how many classes are required, advises that he has completed 2 appointments, has not been able to get there due to health reasons. State advises that program is to be completed. If not completed by next court date, Defendant is to be present in Court. Court questions whether Defendant has to waive right to counsel to speak with State regarding completion of agreement. Defendant waives right to Counsel. Court questions Defendant, finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver. Bond continues as is.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for December 9, 2019 at 03:00 pm.
Deferred prosecution agreement hearing on September 13, 2019 at 11:45 am.

Defendant Jason M Voivedich in court with attorney Tara L. Teesch.  Defendant Jason M Voivedich in custody.  Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters guilty plea to Ct. 1.  Court questions Defendant on rights, finds pleas made freely and voluntarily, withholds acceptance of plea on Ct. 1. Court dismisses Ct. 2 but reads in for sentencing.  Court reviews conditions contained within DJA, approves DJA.   Upon successful completion of DJA, the State will, after 12 months, move to amend charge to a non criminal charge of Battery and matter can be disposed by written stipulation. Bond remains in effect as previously set.  Deferred prosecution agreement hearing scheduled for September 12, 2019 at 11:45 am.

Defendant Jason M Voivedich in court with attorney Tara L. Teesch.  Defendant Jason M Voivedich in custody.  Colleen Catherine Nordin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file, questions counsel where matter is at. Atty Teesch indicates matter will be resolved by way of a DJA, requests a plea date be set as soon as the courts calendar allows.  State has no objection.  Bond remains in effect.  Plea hearing scheduled for September 20, 2018 at 10:00 am.

Defendant Jason M Voivedich appears by video. Aattorney Tara L. Teesch appears in person.  Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews events in file.  Defense waives reading of the complaint, enters not guilty plea. Court finds probable cause for bindover. Bond remains in effect.  Status conference scheduled for September 6, 2018 at 11:45 am.
Defendant was fingerprinted by jail staff.
No violent contact with D.R.      To be fingerprinted and photographed before leaving the Justice Center.
